OL,3,CHow will Reeves' budget reset and
OL,4,Cremake Britain?
OL,6,FWhat's striking is that their means is
OL,7,Fvia higher taxes, borrowing and public
OL,8,Fspending, when all are at or near post-
OL,9,Fwar records.
OL,11,FAnd you'll recall that the two of them
OL,12,Fspent most of the recent general
OL,13,Felection campaign saying they really
OL,14,Fdidn't want to increase taxes, because
OL,15,Fthey'd risen so much in preceding
OL,16,Fyears.
OL,18,FBut Reeves will argue their hand has
OL,19,Fbeen forced by an inheritance from the
OL,20,FTories of crumbling public services
OL,21,Fand unfunded spending over-runs.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
