OL,3,CHow will Reeves' budget reset and
OL,4,Cremake Britain?
OL,6,FBig businesses, by contrast, are
OL,7,Flikely to welcome the budget. They
OL,8,Ffind it easier to absorb the assorted
OL,9,Fincreases to their running costs, they
OL,10,Fwant a predictable stable path for
OL,11,Ftax, spend and borrowing, and the
OL,12,Fpublic-sector investment plans will
OL,13,Fyield significant profitable
OL,14,Fopportunities for them.
OL,16,FIt is in keeping with long political
OL,17,Fhistory for the biggest companies to
OL,18,Fprosper under a Labour government. The
OL,19,Fidea of Labour as a proponent of the
OL,20,Fcorporate state is as old as the mixed
OL,21,Feconomy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
